-- Ukraine Spring-Grain Sowing Reaches 2.1 Million Hectares
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-04-10T07:48:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/ukraine-spring-grain-sowing-reaches-2-1-million-hectares.html
Ukraine’s farmers planted 2.1
million hectares (5.2 million acres) with early spring grain as
of yesterday, or 53 percent of the government’s target,
according to the  Agriculture Ministry .  Farmers started sowing sugar beet and sunflowers, the Kiev-
based ministry said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
